'''上斯劳特'''（Upper Slaughter）是[[英格兰|英格兰]][[格洛斯特郡|格洛斯特郡]][[科茨沃尔德|科茨沃尔德]]区的一个村庄，在[[斯托昂澤沃爾德|斯托昂澤沃爾德]]西南{{convert|4|mi|km}}。
附近的村庄包括[[下斯劳特|下斯劳特]]、[[水上伯顿|水上伯顿]]和戴尔斯福德。

村里的[[圣公会|圣公会]]教堂献给圣彼得<ref>''The Buildings of England'', ed Nikolaus_Pevsner</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Elrington |first=C. R. |authorlink=C. R. Elrington (editor) |title=A History of the County of Gloucester: volume 6 |date=1965 |pages=134–142 |url=http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=66437 |access-date=2020-11-26 |archive-date=2014-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903000709/http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=66437 }}</ref>。

上斯劳特是一座感恩村庄（Thankful Villages）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hellfirecorner.co.uk/thankful.htm |title=The thankful villages by Norman Thorpe, Rod Morris and Tom Morgan |publisher=Hellfirecorner.co.uk |date= |accessdate=9 June 2013 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111225433/http://www.hellfirecorner.co.uk/thankful.htm }}</ref> 是英国少数在[[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]中没有死去任何男人的村庄<ref name=BBC>{{cite news|last=Kelly|first=Jon|title=Thankful villages: The places where everyone came back from the wars|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-15671943|accessdate=11 November 2011|publisher=BBC News|date=11 November 2011|archive-date=2011-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111111131118/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-15671943|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这个村庄在[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]中也没有失去任何男人，因此被称为"双感恩村"。<ref name=BBC/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=66437 |title=Parishes - Upper Slaughter | A History of the County of Gloucester: volume 6 (pp. 134–142) |publisher=British-history.ac.uk |date=4 October 1913 |accessdate=9 June 2013 |archive-date=2014-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903000709/http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=66437 }}</ref>
